iew_profile.asp?Action=View&Profile=0&Id=2114" target="_blank">EquipmentListing</a></font></p><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/8/01 11:02:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Maybe, maybe not.</span><hr size=1> Firstly, I'm not that worried about Giants Bane at all.  I've been on enough giant raids to know that all that spell will do is get me killed faster.  If I get kindly as a side effect to doing other things, fine.  But in no way am I going out of my way.<br><br>And as for SS armor being the best in the game.  Perhapse, BUT... Improving an armor piece by 1 or 2 in the resist, 1 INT which is already maxed, 15 extra mana which is useless even when added to the other armor pieces, getting sleeves that are NO better than Cryosilk except in AC which is worthless because the art of a wizard is being effective and NOT getting hit...   Yeah, its the best in the game.  By a couple points TOPS.  No way is it worth the effort when Kael is easier to fight for the Thurg quests and the coldain are less bothered by faction.<br><br>ToV is fine.  And I hope all the melee and plate classes get their armor because THEIRS are INSANELY better than planes or other quests.  Casters?  Nope.  They are not so far ahead.  Not even close to justify the effort.  Yeah, they are the best.  But a rating of 161 in cold resist is not going to save you so much more than a rating of 160.<br><br>At least make the differences MAJOR.  A better effect, 10 extra resistance points and AC rather than 1 or 2, Mana that might actually make a difference in our pool.  It just doesn't add up to the hardship.<br><br>With Diamond and Blue Diamond jewelry, Resistance specific items, weapons with high resists on them, I can maintain higher resistances than with all the SS armor combined.  I don't mind keeping four changes of clothes in the bank for certain circumstances at all.  But the bottom line is, a wizard can come up with better by being resourceful.  Melee on the other hand are TOTALLY justified in going nuts for SS armor.  Its INCREDIBLE.  SS for casters is the best, yes.  But unimpressive for the work and won't make a major difference in the long run.<br><br>W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarkarius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkarius </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/01 9:19:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maybe, maybe not.</span><hr size=1> Jesus quit complaining. A couple of Kael Arena raids will get you to Ally faction. The armor is better than anything else available to us. If you CAN do the quests then wtf is wrong with having the best armor? I don't care if its not that much better than the thurg quests its BETTER. Better is better. Also the ToV quests are extremely nice. The new boots from Yelinak and the tears quests are awesome. <br><br>And IMO the bane spells are awesome. If you time your nukes and don't go full burn on one of the uber mobs that takes ~10 minutes to kill the damage output from the bane spells is significant. Its easy to get both bane spells and ask anyone wizard who has them and I can guarantee you that against the mobs they work on they would say that the spells are incredible. Being able to do 2k dmg per nuke unresistable is sweet. 2 peridots per cast is nothing. My only gripe is you have to be level 60 for them. Should have another version at 55 or so that does 1200 or 1500 instead of just the big daddy at 60. <p>Arkarius Angelwing <br>54th DE Wiz <br><b>Tides of Destiny <br> </b></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarkarius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkarius </A> at: 5/10/01 9:22:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 7:31:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lol...</span><hr size=1> Easy there hero.  I never said faction was the problem.  I don't mind being on Dragon faction or trying to get it.  It was only a question of relationships.  It wasn't vendictive, a rant, a flame, or whatever.  It was an opinion that I am entitled to.  Just as you are entitled to yours.  I simply wish the prize for all that work (not just faction but the MANY trips to ToV) was as much an improvement as melee armor was for them.  Thats all.  If you check some of the other posts, you'd see that I am one of the advocates that SUPPORT the ease of changing SS faction in Kael faction.  It wasn't meant to be taken as completely devalueing the SS questing process.  I apologize if you took it that way.  BUT, I am simply one being vocal about it.  There are many who think the same thing.  Just as there are many who agree with your side.  I will not discount your opinion since this is a free and open forum.  And yes, the level 60 restriction is on my list as well.<br><br>W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utarrath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tarrath</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 10:30:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lol...</span><hr size=1> I personally dont think the gear in TOV is really all that better then POG stuff. I have both the arms from pog and the arms for SS. All the gear has the same effects and other then some slight differences in 1-2 resist points it isnt that much different. Although the melee chars get great upgrades from pog to SS armor quests.<br><br>Our Warrior did his bp and has 54 ac thats a huge increase unlike our robe which has the same effect as the SS robe or Kael robe.<br><br>If it wasnt for the other chars in my guild upgrades we could just do POG and skip all the faction and other things all together. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WI