t he's saying as I understand things now, the armor just isn't good enough for the hassle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarkarius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkarius </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 2:12:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh, tarrath...</span><hr size=1> Yeah it might not be as good as it should be.. but caster gear never is. Not much you can do about it. CoV faction is extremely easy to get to ally by doing a few Vindicator raids or arena. ToV provides more than the normal quest gear.. items with really nice stats and some pieces with Flowing Thought effects. We're still working on Dozekar so we haven't completed any yet but the ones that have been completed on other servers is really nice. Sorry for going off on ya but people who rant and bitch about Dragon faction kind of piss me off because most of them don't know the true rewards that dragon faction offers. All they can think about is the couple more AC on the Kael armor... <p>Arkarius Angelwing <br>54th DE Wiz <br><b>Tides of Destiny <br> </b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 1:51:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Umm...</span><hr size=1> Perhaps my first post had anger, but it is inappropriate to suggest that we haven't done our homework.  Our opinions were presented properly and chastising us for presenting it is almost rediculous.  Of course there are more things about dragon faction.  That is not what the original post was about.  It wasn't about the value of ToV in general.  It wasn't even about the difficulty of getting faction.  It was about the SS armor.  Nothing more.  How for the quest work, it doesn't add up.  So along this topic, your argument is irrelevant.  It has nothing to do with the original opinion.  I have said dozens of times that the faction is easily obtainable if you have concentrated multi group efforts for upper Kael mobs.  It was a comparison of armor.  Nothing more.  Can we stick to the topic rather than devalue our opinions becuase you simply don't agree?<br><br>W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 1:56:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> anger...</span><hr size=1> yes I'm angry about the faction changes.  But not how they effect everything.  Just the armor.  Thats all.<br><br>W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyaldin111.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaldin111</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 12:28:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Velious</span><hr size=1> Velious has me pissed off altogether, especially with the faction system, the only remotely decent caster stuff really comes from ToV and the boss mobs (velk, kelorek etc) while melee stuff drops like crazy.  Hell Dain and Tormax are chock full of awesome melee armor while they each only have 0-1 piece of caster gear (ring of frost off dain, haven't heard of any caster drops off tormax)  And what makes me even MORE mad is how easy it is to bring up coldain or giant faction, go wack the dain or tormax and then bring it up again.  If you wack tormax or dain, it ought to be like killing lucan where you become KoS or dubious FOREVER.  <br><br>Velious sux! Back to the old world...least the mobs don't proc deadly velium poison...<br><br>Yaldin<br>53 Channeler<br>Karana Server<br>Storm`s Justice <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 8:14:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious</span><hr size=1> For the record, it took me three major Kael raids to go from apprehensive to Ally.  Also have mostly quest armor.  Three pieces of sages, and one icicle.  I have a friend with all icicle.  We have the same effects, yet with some strategic resistance items, I have better overall stats.  The point is, with some thought, you can overcome the extremely small improvement of Icicle over Sages.  Yes, I plan to explore the other quests that require CoV faction.  But this is simply the armor comparison.<br><br>W.F.<br><br>p.s. The above is excluding robes all together.  I have maintained that the Robe of Icicles IS quite a nice addition. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 10:13:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ally Faction?????</span><hr size=1> Being only lvl 43, I have not had the pleasure of either Kael arena raids or ToV raids. However, I have done extensive research on what faction to align with for the best quest armors. After many hours of comparing the rewards for each of the quest for all 3 faction groups, I hardly see any reason to do anything other than the Thurg quests. For the most part, the dorf quests can be completed with 2 50s groups, 1 group if it is well balanced 55+. The minimal stat increases dragon and giants quest rewards give hardly justifies the HUGE investment in time and man power required to hunt ANYTHING in ToV. Good luck going in with 2 groups unless you are in an uber guild and everyone going is 60. Most guilds would have a hard time with 3 or even 4 groups for some of the encounters in ToV. To get enough quest components would require daily raids for weeks. Sure the melees would love their rewards, but the casters would get hosed as usual. I would like to see a mathematical comparison of the quest armor for the melees and the casters. I doesn't take a rocket scientist to figure out that the risk v. reward is much better for the melee than for the caster. Sure, I will eventually end up in ToV, but it will be more for melee gear than caster gear. By that time I should have a nice set of Sage's to wear in while the melees rake in the uber armor.<br><br>Oh well, the price we pay for having the best class I suppose.<br><br>Always a wizard, <p><span style="font-size: 18px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 43rd Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br><i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/01 5:11:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/NEW4.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ally Faction?????</span><hr size=1> There are definitely two schools of thought.  The ally faction for Dragons definitely yields better overall quests.  Not just armor.<br><br>BUT, if you only do the armor comparison, doesn't seem worth it.  I guess its simply a matter or preference and patience to build the faction.  As for armor, I'm very happy with the Sages pieces I have.  Trying to help our melee's get theirs since they have MAJOR upgrades.<br><br>W.F. <p><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith2.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith3.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upolgedra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Polgedra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/20/01 4:24:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ally Faction?????</span><hr size=1> Well I'm upset at the change to the faction - i was on amiable and did my gloves and boots now i have a tattered robe and three pristene emeralds and i gotta hunt in kael for faction all over again. I was planning to get faction up for the bane spell but could take my time and time it with getting lvl 60 now im rushing to become an ally for my new robe and this is fun ? Well imho they should not have changed the faction once it had been set as those who did their quests befor the nerf have a distinct advantage in duels pvp and BOTB. As for the diffs in armour? sure they are all pretty similar except for the bracers. SS bracer puts the others to shame. when all the ss armour vs pog kael or thurg is compared the real diffs is mana and hp. I havnt added everything exactly but in simple comparisons the full ss armour will give a wizard roughly 200 hp and about 50 mana extra - add the added little resists ad we are looking at about plus 5 in all stats better. AC is not really an issue unless it is 20 ac diffs which it is not in total so pvp duels and botb would see a full ss vs thurg pog or kael- all other things being equal; win.<br><br>Fortunbas<br>59 evoker <br>Bristlebane<br>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 11:15:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/NEW4.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ally Faction?????</span><hr size=1> I agree with the points in an SS vs Thurg sense.   The one option that is being ruled out is the ability to find &quot;mix and match&quot; items all over the planet that would actually exceed both sets of quest armor.  Yes, the hassle of finding them is great, but at the same time, one could do it with a ton of patience and concentrated effort.  If the BotB situation came more frequently, then I would be STREAKING to get all SS armor.  I kinda wish it did.<br><br>W.F. <p><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http:/